# FANUC Fieldbus Rule

Apply when specifying I/O maps, UOP wiring, PNS selection, or writing code that handshakes with an external PLC / HMI / press brake.

## Handshake flavors

FANUC supports several program-select patterns. Pick one, document it, don't mix.

### PNS (Program Number Select)

- External selects a program via `UI[9..16]` as a binary number.
- Strobe pulse on `UI[17] PNSTROBE`.
- Robot ACKs via `UO[11..18] PNS_ACK1..8` and `UO[10] SNACK`.
- Robot starts on `UI[18] PROD_START` (edge, not level).

### Style Select (SDI)

- Uses Style inputs configured via System / UOP / Style menu.
- Looks up style via Style Table to a program.

### RSR (Robot Service Request)

- Legacy; avoid on new integrations.

## UOP signal baseline (R-30iB)

| Signal | Index | Direction | Meaning |
|--------|-------|-----------|---------|
| IMSTP | UI[1] | In | Immediate stop (Cat 0 / Cat 1 per config) |
| HOLD | UI[2] | In | Pause (Cat 2) |
| SFSPD | UI[3] | In | Safety speed (teach limit) |
| CSTOPI | UI[4] | In | Cycle stop |
| FAULT_RESET | UI[5] | In | Clear active alarm |
| START | UI[6] | In | Continue / start from paused |
| HOME | UI[7] | In | Custom per integration (not standard) |
| ENBL | UI[8] | In | Robot enabled; must be ON for motion |
| RSR1..8 / PNS1..8 | UI[9..16] | In | Program number select bits |
| PNSTROBE | UI[17] | In | Strobe PNS bits |
| PROD_START | UI[18] | In | Start selected program |
| CMDENBL | UO[1] | Out | Command enable |
| SYSRDY | UO[2] | Out | System ready |
| PROGRUN | UO[3] | Out | Program running |
| PAUSED | UO[4] | Out | Program paused |
| HELD | UO[5] | Out | Held |
| FAULT | UO[6] | Out | Fault active |
| ATPERCH | UO[7] | Out | At perch (home) |
| TPENBL | UO[8] | Out | Teach pendant enabled |
| BATALM | UO[9] | Out | Battery alarm |
| BUSY | UO[10] | Out | Busy |
| ACK1..8 / SNO1..8 | UO[11..18] | Out | PNS ack |

Always confirm indices against the specific integration's controller config; some OEM builds shift the mapping.

## PLC side (EtherNet/IP or Profinet master)

- Always hold `IMSTP`, `HOLD`, `SFSPD`, `ENBL` high at steady state.
- Pulse `FAULT_RESET` (rising edge) to clear faults. Do not hold high.
- Wait for `CMDENBL` and `SYSRDY` before asserting `PROD_START`.
- Verify `PROGRUN` transitions to ON after `PROD_START`, or treat as a start failure.

## Group signals

- `GI[]` / `GO[]`: bitfields mapped from DI/DO ranges. Used for part IDs, style codes, error codes.
- Document bit ordering (MSB vs LSB, which DI carries bit 0) in `INTEGRATION_SPEC_*.md`.

## Anti-patterns

- Asserting `PROD_START` as a level instead of an edge.
- Asserting multiple `PNS` bits without a strobe.
- Polling `PROGRUN` without a timeout.
- Mapping fault recovery to a single `FAULT_RESET` without a supervisor inspection checklist.
- Using `DI[]/DO[]` for program-select when PNS is available.

## Modbus TCP (press-brake and third-party integrations)

Handled via a KAREL or PC SDK bridge (see `tools/mqtt_bridge/` or a customer-specific KAREL). Canon: `fanuc_dataset/normalized/protocols/ONE_press_brake_modbus_integration.md`.

